The article discusses President Obama's proposal to invest $25 billion in school infrastructure to modernize public schools across the country. The funds can be used for various projects such as repair and renovation, energy efficiency upgrades, asbestos removal, and building new science and computer labs. Additionally, the President is proposing a $5 billion investment in community colleges to modernize their infrastructure. The article provides a breakdown of the funding each state could receive for K-12 schools and community colleges. It also highlights the need for these investments, as many public school buildings are old and in need of repair, and community colleges require upgrades to meet the demands of the 21st-century workforce.